{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1015","heading":"Definitions","label":"1015 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch18A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2020—Pars. (2) to (6). , (2), added par. (2) and redesignated former pars. (2) to (5) as (3) to (6), respectively. Former par. (6) redesignated (7).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(1)Par. (6)(B)(i)(X). , added subcl. (X).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(3)Par. (7). , redesignated par. (6) as (7).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(1)Par. (7)(C). , inserted “, including benefits to fisheries, wildlife, or habitat” after “river or stream”.Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(4)"],"amendments":["Amendments2020—Pars. (2) to (6). , (2), added par. (2) and redesignated former pars. (2) to (5) as (3) to (6), respectively. Former par. (6) redesignated (7).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(1)Par. (6)(B)(i)(X). , added subcl. (X).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(3)Par. (7). , redesignated par. (6) as (7).Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(1)Par. (7)(C). , inserted “, including benefits to fisheries, wildlife, or habitat” after “river or stream”.Pub. L. 116–260, § 1107(a)(4)"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Affected stakeholder","label":"1 Affected stakeholder","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “affected stakeholder” means an entity that significantly affects, or is significantly affected by, the quality or quantity of water in a watershed, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Disadvantaged community","label":"2 Disadvantaged community","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “disadvantaged community” means a community (including a city, town, county, or reasonably isolated and divisible segment of a larger municipality) with an annual median household income that is less than 100 percent of the statewide annual median household income for the State in which the community is located, according to the most recent decennial census.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Grant recipient","label":"3 Grant recipient","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “grant recipient” means a watershed group that the Secretary has selected to receive a grant under .section 1015a(c)(2) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Program","label":"4 Program","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “program” means the Cooperative Watershed Management Program established by the Secretary under .section 1015a(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Secretary","label":"5 Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1015","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs1015%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.","notes":[],"amendme